    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nIn Neovim 0.9.4 I can capture and highlight parentheses in macros in C code, but it doesn't seem to work in 0.10.\r\n\r\n0.9.4:\r\n<img width=\"160\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-01 at 16 15 45\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/7075380/d8694b61-415d-4c0e-b67a-5989d4c833a4\">\r\n\r\n0.10:\r\n<img width=\"154\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-01 at 16 14 48\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/7075380/6d6b2eda-29be-419f-b7f6-a6401748610c\">\r\n\r\nI think in general there is a problem with capturing stuff inside a macro in 0.10:\r\n<img width=\"1702\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-01 at 16 14 22\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/7075380/6a2e5d94-cb41-4056-96c2-112a0eda8b16\">\r\n\r\nNote: The above doesn't capture anything. This shouldn't be because of the ERROR, since we can usually capture inside an ERROR like here:\r\n<img width=\"1694\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-01 at 16 24 11\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/7075380/9d12bc91-5f49-4d5d-aaf5-64b2437f71c9\">\r\n\r\nI wanted to test something similar for 0.9.4 and show that we can capture it there, but I don't think there is something like the query editor in 0.9.4? Is there some way I could better test this?\r\n\r\nAlso, is this considered a neovim bug or a parser bug? (Should I report this somewhere else?)\r\n\r\nNote: The `c` parser parses macros using language injections, if that helps clarify what might be causing this issue. \r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`nvim test.c`\r\nWrite: `#define TEST (-1)`\r\n`:w<CR>`\r\n`:InspectTree<CR>`\r\n`o`\r\nWrite `(parenthesized_expression) @test` in the query editor (or `(number_literal) @test`) and place the cursor on `@test` in normal mode.\r\n\r\nNote that we can't capture any of the above.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nLike my last picture above, we should capture the corresponding queries. \r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-2005+gf69658bc3-Homebrew\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.2.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nwezterm\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nwezterm\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
    "closed_at": "2024-01-01T15:47:27Z",
    "comment_data": [
