            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Yes, we have tightened up (improved) the self-injections for macros. Feel free to customize the injection queries if you want different highlighting.\r\n> \r\n> (And homebrew nightly \"releases\" -- as opposed to actual releases -- don't come with treesitter parsers, so make sure this is not the issue you're seeing. Also make sure you're not using the nvim-treesitter queries, which may - intentionally -- differ.)\r\n\r\nI have the parsers installed, and I mainly made this issue to see if I could figure out what causes this problem. From what I can tell it was a problem with my queries, but what confused me was that the `c` parser and `rust` parser work differently, so I have to write language specific code that I didn't think would be necessary. (Rust also uses language injections for macros, but they don't work the exact same way.)",
