            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Yes, because macros don't work the exact same way. Queries very much are language-specific.\r\n\r\nI think I was a bit unclear, I know about the difference in the queries. What I needed to do was different behavior in `LanguageTree:register_cbs { on_changedtree = function(changes, tree) ... end }` based on the language, which I hadn't needed for any language other than c/cpp. \r\n\r\nAnyways, thank you for the quick responses. ",
